recent surveys have revealed a lack of close - in planets around evolved stars more massive than 1.2 . such planets are common around solar - mass stars . we have calculated the orbital evolution of planets around stars with a range of initial masses , and have shown how planetary orbits are affected by the evolution of the stars all the way to the tip of the red giant branch ( rgb ) . we find that tidal interaction can lead to the engulfment of close - in planets by evolved stars . the engulfment is more efficient for
