upper quarter of fig . 2 is the region where broad " bands are formed . these bands have a finite width in the -direction , and the particles occupying these states will have a finite mobility in the longitudinal direction . the other set of narrow " bands occupies the left and right quarters of fig . 2 . from the point of view of the kronig - penney model ( [ eq : kronig ] ) they correspond to the valence bands of the periodic potential . these bands are infinitesimally narrow in the -direction , and electrons
